{
  "texts": [
    "This indicates that our ML model, even in cases with a high RMAE, can sufficiently explain the overall variance of the measurements as the R 2 values are acceptable.",
    "Although RMAE and R 2 are widely accepted metrics for evaluating ML model performance, their lack of physical significance may lead to misplaced confidence in the model's performance from a physical standpoint (e.g.",
    "Wang et al. 2020; Hora & Giometto 2023).",
    "Here, we turn our attention to examining the accuracy of the ML model in predicting the wave-phase-dependent distribution of skin-friction drag over surface waves.",
    "The stress distributions over waves are largely wave-phase dependent, and accurate predictions of stress distributions are of significant importance for numerical simulations such as wall-modelled LESs and developing sea-state-dependent modelling frameworks."
  ]
}